      <field name="fulltext">[Peter's Denial]</field>
      <field name="fulltext">here xal þe woman come to jewys and seyn ia ancilla What serys how take ?e on with þis man se ?e not on of hese dysciplys how he be-heldyth ?ou þan. here xal þe tother woman seyn to petyr ija ancille A good man me semyth be þe þat þou on of his dysciplys xulde be. Petrus A woman I sey nevyr er þis man syn þat þis werd fyrst be-gan et cantabit gallus. ia Ancilla What þou mayst not sey nay þou art on of hese men be þi face wel we may þe ken. Petrus Woman þou seyst A-mys of me I knowe hym not so mote I the. ius judeus A fela myn wel met for my cosynys ere pou of smet Whan we þi mayster in þe ?erd toke þan all þi ffelawys hym for-soke and now þou mayst not hym for-sake for þou art of galyle I vndyr-take. Petrus Sere I knowe hym not be hym þat made me and ?e wole me be-leve ffor An oth I take record of all þis companye þat I sey to ?ow is soth et cantabit gallus. And þan jhesus xal lokyn on petyr and petyr xal wepyn and þan he xal gon out and seyn A weel a-way weel away fals hert why whylt þou not brest Syn þi maystyr so cowardly þou hast forsake Alas qwher xal I now on erthe rest tyl he of his mercy to grace wole me take. I haue for-sake my mayster and my lord jhesu thre tymes as he tolde me þat I xulde do þe same Wherfore I may not haue sorwe A-now I synful creature am so mech to blame. Whan I herd þe cok crowyn he kest on me A loke As who seyth be-thynke þe what I seyd be-fore Alas þe tyme þat I evyr hym for-soke And so wyl I thynkyn from hens evyr more.</field>
